### XML Format Specification

Return a valid, well-formed XML document.

### Rules
- Root element must be `<page>` with attribute `number="{{pageNumber}}"`.
- Each paragraph is a `<p>` element.
- Headings use `<h1>`, `<h2>`, etc. based on visual hierarchy.
- Lists use `<ul>` / `<li>` tags.
- Tables use `<table>`, `<row>`, `<cell>` tags.
- Images use `<image id="" description=""/>`.
- All text content must be properly escaped.
- Maintain exact reading order from the document.

### Example Output
```xml
<page number="1">
  <h1>Report Summary</h1>
  <p>This report outlines Q1 performance metrics.</p>
  <table>
    <row><cell>Metric</cell><cell>Value</cell></row>
    <row><cell>Revenue</cell><cell>$500,000</cell></row>
  </table>
  <image id="1.1img" description="Company logo top-left"/>
</page>